<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="165" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="165">
Total body length ranged within 11.8 and 13.7 mm. Tail 23.4-24.9% of body length. Hooks 6-7. Anterior 10-13 and posterior teeth 16-25. Rigid and opaque body (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. A Serratosagitta pacifica (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704197" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">13A</figureCitation>
). Small head (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. A Serratosagitta pacifica (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704197" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">13A, B</figureCitation>
). Grasping spines serrated on edge (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Grasping spine A abruptly curved hooks (Krohnitta subtilis, Krohnittidae) B gently curved and not serrated hooks (Ferosagitta robusta, Sagittidae) C gently curved and serrated hooks (Serratosagitta pacifica, Sagittidae)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704192" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">8C</figureCitation>
). Collarette absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Position and shape of corona ciliata A Aidanosagitta regularis B Pterosagitta draco C Serratosagitta pacifica D Flaccisagitta enflata." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704194" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">10C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. A Serratosagitta pacifica (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704197" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">13A</figureCitation>
). Rectangular eyes with 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“T”">&quot;T&quot;</normalizedToken>
shaped eye pigments (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. A Serratosagitta pacifica (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704197" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">13B</figureCitation>
). Intestinal diverticula absent (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Position and shape of corona ciliata A Aidanosagitta regularis B Pterosagitta draco C Serratosagitta pacifica D Flaccisagitta enflata." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704194" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">10C</figureCitation>
). Anterior fins spanned 21.9% of body length. Anterior fins completely rayed beginning between ventral ganglion and caudal septum. Starting point of anterior fins 34.6% and ending points of anterior fins 55.1% of body length, respectively (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. A Serratosagitta pacifica (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704197" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">13A, D</figureCitation>
). Posterior fins 26.2% of body length and 1.2 times longer than anterior fins. Starting points of posterior fins 63.7% and ending points of posterior fins 89.7% of body length, respectively. Posterior fins well-separated from anterior fins (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. A Serratosagitta pacifica (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704197" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">13A, E</figureCitation>
). Caudal fin triangular shaped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. A Serratosagitta pacifica (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704197" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">13A, C</figureCitation>
). Seminal vesicles touched or closed to lateral fins and well-separated from tail fin (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. A Serratosagitta pacifica (dorsal view) B head C tail D anterior fin E posterior fin. Abbreviations: AF = anterior fin; AT = anterior teeth; CC = corona ciliata; COL = collarette; E = eye; PF = posterior fin; PT = posterior teeth; SV = seminal vesicle." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704197" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">13C</figureCitation>
) with elongated knob facing obliquely forward and teeth-like appendages forming 5-10 distal protrusions. Eggs reached anterior of anterior fins. Collarette beginning in front of eyes and extended over neck (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figure 10. Position and shape of corona ciliata A Aidanosagitta regularis B Pterosagitta draco C Serratosagitta pacifica D Flaccisagitta enflata." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1106.80184.figure10" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/704194" pageId="0" pageNumber="165">10C</figureCitation>
, 
